1
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:14,000
♪ You're the only one in my heart ♪

2
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,960
♪ Even if you never know ♪

3
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:19,760
♪ I'll keep watching over you ♪

4
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:23,400
♪ I love you more than words
But our path isn't easy ♪

5
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:27,000
♪ I just need you to believe in me ♪

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,640
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

7
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:34,640
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

8
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:41,440
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

9
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:44,880
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

10
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:46,920
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

11
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:51,080
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

12
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:55,040
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

13
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:59,760
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

14
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:03,400
Would it kill you
to admit you chose the wrong partner?

15
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,680
I regret marrying you more than anything.

16
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,600
Are you both sure about this divorce?

17
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:09,640
We've both agreed on it.

18
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:12,480
No one here knows us.
So why are you being nice to me?

19
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:16,840
I was just helping an old woman
so she wouldn't starve to death.

20
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:18,200
Mom!

21
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,440
Runch…

22
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,200
Wait, Runch.

23
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,600
Listen, I really didn't mean it.

24
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,760
You should go home.

25
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:33,480
Are you mad at me?

26
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:37,880
Runch…

27
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,720
Runch…

28
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,640
Peeracha…

29
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,920
Let me treat your wound.

30
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,760
Don't.

31
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,720
I have to.

32
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:12,680
My mom's the reason you got hurt.

33
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,360
Ow! It stings!

34
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,520
It stings!

35
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,680
Try to bear with it, okay?

36
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,840
I'll clean around the wound first.

37
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,760
Ow, ow…

38
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,880
It shouldn't hurt much, Neen.

39
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,040
I'm just cleaning around it.

40
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,800
I'm not touching the wound.

41
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,440
This might sting a little.

42
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,200
There, all done.

43
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:03,320
I'm sorry on my mom's behalf.

44
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,120
I'll walk you up to your room.

45
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,360
No.

46
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:59,240
It's because you're like this…

47
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,360
that I can never get over you.

48
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,080
Ms. Warin, have you really
thought this through?

49
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:23,920
Filing for divorce means digging up
every part of your marriage.

50
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,240
Some things may hurt more than you expect.

51
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:31,000
I've been hurting for so long.

52
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,960
I can't even feel anything anymore.

53
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:38,840
My husband has a habit
of giving me false hope.

54
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:43,640
He only treats me well
in front of other people.

55
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:48,280
But at home,
he only spends time with his parents.

56
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:51,720
It's like I don't even exist.

57
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,840
I don't want to live
with someone like that anymore.

58
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:03,040
Then let's start with the marital assets.

59
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:07,600
The house, cars, savings, shares…

60
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,760
everything acquired during the marriage.

61
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,640
Do you have proof
that they were acquired together

62
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,320
or that you shared the expenses?

63
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,800
Yes. But I handled everything on my own.

64
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,160
He never contributed at all.

65
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:25,440
Assets acquired during a marriage

66
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:27,880
are considered marital property by law…

67
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,560
They belong to both parties.

68
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:37,240
Salaries or any assets purchased
or obtained during the marriage,

69
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:39,280
even if they're under only one person's name,

70
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,560
are still considered marital property.

71
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,240
How about this…

72
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:47,360
I'll handle everything for you.

73
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,360
You don't have to go through this alone.

74
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,280
Sometimes…

75
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,080
we don't really need much.

76
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:00,600
We just want to know that the people we love

77
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,920
are on our side.

78
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:05,320
And sometimes, the one who loves the most

79
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:08,440
ends up the most exhausted.

80
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:11,320
You seem to understand
that feeling very well.

81
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,720
Well, it's my job to understand my clients.

82
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,320
Come on, guys!

83
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,080
It's Friday. We should go party.

84
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,680
Same place?

85
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,440
Sure.

86
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,920
But are you paying?

87
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,360
Because if not, I'm not going.

88
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,520
Come on…

89
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,080
Boss.

90
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:44,280
Our department's going out tonight,

91
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:46,880
so we were hoping…

92
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,720
you'd treat us.

93
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,960
Does everyone want to go?

94
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,360
Yes.

95
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:57,960
Everyone has been working really hard lately.

96
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,840
We could use

97
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,080
a little morale boost.

98
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,400
Of course.

99
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,920
Order whatever you want.

100
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,200
But I'm coming too.

101
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,400
You are?

102
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:14,800
Of course.

103
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:19,040
I've never joined our department parties.

104
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:22,880
I want to see how hard everyone
has been working.

105
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,160
I'd also like a chance to talk to all of you…

106
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:29,240
not just as your boss,
but as part of the team.

107
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,559
See you there, okay?

108
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,440
Yes.

109
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,840
I don't think this is going
to be fun anymore.

110
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:42,840
Says who?

111
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,160
It's going to be even more fun now.

112
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,000
Come on, everyone.

113
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,600
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

114
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,680
Come on, Boss.

115
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,720
Why aren't you drinking?

116
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,440
Drink!

117
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:08,880
Drink! Drink!

118
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:11,040
Drink! Drink!

119
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,320
-Yay!
-Yay!

120
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,560
Geez, Boss.

121
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:23,200
Does your wife only let you drink
smooth, fancy, expensive wine?

122
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,280
One taste of cheap liquor

123
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,960
and you're already wasted.

124
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,000
That's enough, Utt.

125
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,640
Stop trying to get her drunk.

126
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,920
What's wrong with that?

127
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,840
Hey,

128
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,320
fill my glass.

129
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:39,560
Boss, should we call Ms. Peeracha
to pick you up?

130
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,200
Hey.

131
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:44,480
If I call her,

132
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,200
she probably won't answer.

133
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,800
Can you call her for me?

134
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:55,280
I'll dial the number for you.

135
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,000
It's…

136
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,880
It's this one.

137
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,720
I'll call her right now.

138
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,920
Hello?

139
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,440
Huh?

140
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:31,760
Runch is really drunk?

141
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:36,280
Okay, I'm coming right now.

142
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,040
Yes, thank you so much. Bye.

143
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,440
Ugh.

144
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,960
Why is she drunk again?

145
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,840
Hey, Boss.

146
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:57,680
Boss?

147
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,160
Let's be real, okay?

148
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,600
The fancy car you drive,

149
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,920
that ten-million-baht house
in a gated community,

150
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,120
and all those designer clothes…

151
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,280
your wife bought all of them for you?

152
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,080
Wow, Boss.

153
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,960
You really lucked out!

154
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,600
Stop talking like that.

155
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,160
Come on, Boss.

156
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,080
Did the alcohol get to you?

157
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,960
I'm only joking.

158
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:29,760
Everyone already knows
you're living off your wife.

159
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,120
I see.

160
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,040
You're jealous, aren't you?

161
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,760
Because my wife's hot,

162
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,520
rich…

163
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:47,960
and she actually loves me.

164
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,200
Unlike you…

165
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,160
You're just nobody…

166
00:11:57,240 --> 00:12:00,040
depending on some middle-aged women

167
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,760
just to climb higher.

168
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:07,000
And you're terrible at your job too.

169
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,760
All you're good at is sucking up to people.

170
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,480
Say that again.

171
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,520
Want to know…

172
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:19,520
how people really see you?

173
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,800
You're dragging this department down.

174
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,000
You suck at your job,

175
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:31,880
all you do is run your mouth,

176
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,880
suck up to your superiors,

177
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:38,280
and turn people against each other.

178
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,640
Don't push it.

179
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:43,960
Just because your wife is rich
doesn't mean you can say what you want.

180
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:44,920
So what?

181
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,600
What if my wife is rich?

182
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,840
That has nothing to do with this.

183
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,600
I'm just telling the truth.

184
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,880
Your wife…

185
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,640
people like her don't really love anyone.

186
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,640
Everyone knows you're just a trophy wife.

187
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,520
-Utt!
-Utt.

188
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:08,720
If you talk about Neen
like that one more time…

189
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:12,880
I'll make sure you never speak again.

190
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:14,160
Damn it!

191
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,600
-Hey, stop!
-Utt!

192
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,000
Hey!

193
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:22,400
If you ever touch Runch again,

194
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,280
I'll have my uncle fire you.

195
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,400
Runch, let's go home.

196
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:47,320
You know you can't handle alcohol,

197
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,600
and you still drank.

198
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,320
Right?

199
00:13:53,440 --> 00:14:00,040
But he said
you only let me drink expensive wine.

200
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:03,160
The smooth kind

201
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,520
that goes down easily.

202
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:11,400
He said I can't handle cheap liquor.

203
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:17,480
It's like how I can't eat fermented fish.

204
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,640
He said…

205
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,120
ever since I married someone rich,

206
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:26,960
I've become too fancy for it.

207
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,040
Come on, Runch.

208
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,040
-Ugh…
-Just sit down first.

209
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:36,960
I really don't get it. Why?

210
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:42,200
Why does everything have to come back

211
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:44,600
to me marrying someone rich?
What's so wrong about it?

212
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:49,480
They keep saying I hit the jackpot,

213
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:53,160
but I didn't marry you for money, okay?

214
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,600
Does being married to me

215
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,280
hurt your pride that much?

216
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:00,920
No…

217
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:04,760
Then maybe we should hurry up
and get divorced,

218
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,520
so you can finally live
the kind of life you're proud of.

219
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:18,160
Runch?

220
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:23,760
I asked Utt if he was jealous of me

221
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:28,480
because my wife is beautiful, rich,

222
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,320
and kind.

223
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:35,080
I know he is,

224
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,880
because I have someone like you.

225
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:44,160
And I know he has been with older women

226
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:48,080
to climb higher at work.

227
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:51,480
You actually said all that to him?

228
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:53,840
I did.

229
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:56,120
And how would you know that?

230
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:59,160
I saw them once.

231
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:05,800
They were all over each other.

232
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,160
You really drank a lot tonight, huh?

233
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,880
You're usually not like this
when you're drunk.

234
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,320
No…

235
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,640
I'm not drunk.

236
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,640
Maybe a little.

237
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:31,800
But not that drunk, okay?

238
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,000
It's just…

239
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,520
my patience is worse than usual.

240
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,440
Ugh…

241
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,520
Even I'm surprised

242
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,200
at myself.

243
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,160
Mm. That's good.

244
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,920
It is?

245
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:55,000
You want me to stop being patient?

246
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:58,400
Because you've been too patient,

247
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:01,640
we ended up like this.

248
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:13,880
But I'm not imagining it, right?

249
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:19,359
You've been a lot nicer to me today.

250
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,560
Neen…

251
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,840
if that's true,

252
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:33,200
can you spoil me a little more?

253
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:37,360
What do you want?

254
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,840
Can I sleep here with you?

255
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:47,840
Please? Let me stay here tonight.

256
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,880
Neen…

257
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:59,720
I can really sleep here tonight, right?

258
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:04,000
Just go back to your room
if you're going to keep asking.

259
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,200
I guess I won't ask then.

260
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:09,880
I'll stop asking.

261
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:18,280
Thank you for picking me up.

262
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,640
And…

263
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,840
for letting me sleep in here.

264
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,840
Thank you so much.

265
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,920
Are you done? I'm going to sleep.

266
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,480
Whoa…

267
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,560
Neen.

268
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:45,200
Do you really have to put
a bolster between us?

269
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:46,720
Just go to sleep already.

270
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:58,520
Not even a little…

271
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:34,200
What are you doing?

272
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:38,080
Hugging you, obviously.

273
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:43,000
Just let me hold you.
I won't do anything else.

274
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:44,760
Let go.

275
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:46,080
No.

276
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,200
I said let go.

277
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:51,600
Nope.

278
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,520
Nope?

279
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:57,960
♪ In the moments when we look at each other ♪

280
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,840
♪ Even if I don't say it out loud ♪

281
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:04,520
♪ Deep inside, I only care about you ♪

282
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:08,000
♪ Love is so magical ♪

283
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:12,920
♪ Even though sometimes
I don't treat you right ♪

284
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:15,720
♪ And there aren't many sweet words ♪

285
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:18,080
♪ But I want you to know that ♪

286
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:22,760
♪ My life partner will always be you ♪

287
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:26,600
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

288
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:30,600
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

289
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:36,520
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

290
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:41,080
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

291
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:44,880
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

292
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:47,160
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

293
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:52,320
♪ Our touches will make you understand ♪

294
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:55,840
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

295
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:57,720
♪ Use the feeling you know ♪

296
00:20:57,720 --> 00:21:01,880
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

297
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:05,920
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

298
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:09,400
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

299
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:25,920
You're only having coffee?

300
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:29,480
You're only having coffee too.

301
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:33,240
I'm not really hungry.

302
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,320
I'm still full…

303
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:39,160
from last night.

304
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,560
Pervert.

305
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:42,880
How am I the pervert?

306
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,800
I was talking about dinner last night.

307
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:48,320
What were you thinking?

308
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,200
Go to work already.

309
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:56,920
Wait…

310
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,440
Hmm?

311
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,560
Do you want to have lunch together?

312
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:09,640
We should only eat together
when it's necessary.

313
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,840
Have I already used up all your kindness?

314
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:20,120
As long as we don't fight to the point
it affects our mental health,

315
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:21,640
that's good enough for me.

316
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:25,680
I see.

317
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,800
As for last night…

318
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:31,480
we hadn't been close like that in a while.

319
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,840
It's only natural it happened.

320
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:37,360
So we'll just treat it
like we both had a good time.

321
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:51,000
Does that mean…

322
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,200
while the divorce isn't finalized,

323
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:56,720
I can sleep with you anytime I want?

324
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:05,320
That kind of thing still needs my consent.

325
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:09,240
If you want it but I don't,

326
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,680
then it's not happening.

327
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,760
Then whenever you feel like it,

328
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:22,920
you can just call me.

329
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:28,680
Or make the first move like last night, okay?

330
00:23:37,120 --> 00:23:38,800
See you at lunch!

331
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:47,640
If you guys hadn't stopped me,

332
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,960
I would've hit her back last night.

333
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,480
I don't care if she's a woman.

334
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:52,600
Geez, Utt…

335
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:53,800
What?

336
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:57,040
She thinks she can do whatever she wants?

337
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:58,880
She humiliated me in front of everyone

338
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,840
like I'm nothing.

339
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:02,040
What,

340
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:04,520
just because she has connections
and a rich wife,

341
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,360
she thinks she's untouchable?

342
00:24:06,360 --> 00:24:08,360
Hey, keep it down. Someone might hear you.

343
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,560
I don't care!

344
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:11,200
I'm telling you,

345
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,360
she was lucky I wasn't that drunk.

346
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:14,240
Otherwise--

347
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,600
Otherwise, what?

348
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:27,040
I heard everything you just said.

349
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:33,520
I'll say this once.

350
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,360
Don't talk about me behind my back.

351
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,320
Say it to my face.

352
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,240
Be a man.

353
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,640
Starting today,

354
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,800
if anyone has an issue with me,

355
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:51,160
come directly to me.

356
00:24:53,360 --> 00:24:57,680
This is a workplace,
not a street market for gossip.

357
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,240
And one more thing…

358
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:10,320
if you're better at gossiping than working,

359
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:14,800
I'll have to reconsider your position here.

360
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:20,440
Since you think
I'm only here because of connections,

361
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,080
because I have a powerful backing,

362
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:26,160
because my wife's family owns this company…

363
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:30,640
then I'll make use of the resources I have

364
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,440
for the sake of the company.

365
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:36,520
Let's see who's actually working…

366
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:39,520
and who's dragging everyone down.

367
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:30,960
This is never-ending…

368
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,800
Come in.

369
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:22,160
Your lunch is here.

370
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:27,960
You're really sneaky,
bringing lunch up here like this.

371
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:29,360
How so?

372
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:32,440
Afraid I'd refuse to eat with you?

373
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:33,720
That's right.

374
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:36,680
So you're forcing my hand.

375
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:44,360
Here.

376
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,640
Have some.

377
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:02,600
If this makes people think
we're still in love, then fine.

378
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:08,680
There are plenty of ways

379
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,960
to make it look like we're in love.

380
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:13,160
Really?

381
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:14,840
Then let's do all of them.

382
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:16,320
You're serious?

383
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,160
Not that kind of all of them.

384
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:26,800
Too obvious?

385
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,280
Then…

386
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:35,520
Hey!

387
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:38,840
I'll settle for this.

388
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:50,280
But now…

389
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:53,800
I want to kiss you for real.

390
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,800
We're in Thailand, remember?

391
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:01,000
Even if we're married,

392
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:04,360
kissing in public isn't appropriate.

393
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:08,080
I miss when we were abroad.

394
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:12,400
We could kiss anytime, anywhere.

395
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:15,920
Come on.

396
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,920
Go back to your seat.

397
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:20,600
Move.

398
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:35,960
Yes, Mom?

399
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:40,360
I will.

400
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:41,680
Okay.

401
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:44,920
Everything okay?

402
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:49,160
My dad isn't home today,

403
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,240
so my mom wants me to stay over.

404
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:54,640
Are you telling me,
or hinting that I should go too?

405
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:59,520
If I asked… would you come?

406
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:00,440
Ugh!

407
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:03,800
Seeing her would only ruin my mood.

408
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,600
I figured.

409
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:08,640
Hold on…

410
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,880
If I don't go,

411
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:15,520
your mom will probably be too happy.

412
00:30:16,760 --> 00:30:18,200
I've changed my mind.

413
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:19,920
I'm coming too.

414
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:21,480
You mean…

415
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,520
you're coming with me?

416
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:24,640
Yeah.

417
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:27,000
What?

418
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:34,560
I can't come?

419
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:39,720
She hasn't seen her daughter-in-law in days.

420
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:42,120
She must be dying to see me.

421
00:30:42,760 --> 00:30:45,120
You two always fight whenever you meet.

422
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:47,360
Wouldn't it be better to avoid each other?

423
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:51,360
What, scared I'll verbally take her down?

424
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,200
Neen…

425
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:58,400
I'll do whatever it takes
to make that hag miserable.

426
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:04,480
Here you go.

427
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:05,680
Thank you so much.

428
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,000
What did you order?

429
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:19,520
It's not often I get to stay
over at your mom's,

430
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:23,320
so I thought I'd cook something for her.

431
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:28,920
What are you even going to make?

432
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:32,640
I'm not telling you. It's a surprise.

433
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,400
You'll see soon enough.

434
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:55,960
Neen, maybe you should cover up a bit.

435
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:57,640
No.

436
00:31:57,920 --> 00:32:01,080
I like it like this. You like women
who dress like this, don't you?

437
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:04,960
I don't like any women dressing like that.

438
00:32:05,520 --> 00:32:08,040
I only like you like that.

439
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:14,080
Hey, wait for me!

440
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:27,160
Hello, Mother.

441
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:30,520
I thought you were coming alone.

442
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:33,240
I actually told her to come alone,

443
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:35,480
but she's so persistent.

444
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:36,640
Why would she be?

445
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:39,560
She comes here all the time.
That's never been an issue.

446
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:42,600
Oh, there's always an issue when we're apart.

447
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:44,680
She just doesn't say it to you.

448
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:46,640
She only tells me.

449
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:51,400
How could she admit
she can't be away from her wife?

450
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:53,320
That would just upset you, Mother.

451
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:56,600
I didn't expect both of you,

452
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:59,000
so I didn't prepare enough food.

453
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:01,400
That's completely fine, Mother.

454
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:05,160
I'll be your chef for today.

455
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:08,040
I promise you'll love it.

456
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,720
What's going on?

457
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,720
What exactly are you making?

458
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:41,840
Can you tell me now?

459
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:45,560
Not yet.

460
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:47,360
Go sit with your mom.

461
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:51,080
I promise it'll be unqiue.

462
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,240
Shoo, go on.

463
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:18,239
She won't tell you what she's making?

464
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,320
Nope.

465
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:21,400
She's not planning to poison me, is she?

466
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:24,159
Neen isn't that kind of person, Mom.

467
00:34:24,159 --> 00:34:26,960
Hah! She hates me more than anything.

468
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,199
You really think I don't know?

469
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,719
And I know you hate her too.

470
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:37,159
Neen?

471
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,280
-Neen!
-Honey!

472
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,760
What is going on?

473
00:34:51,239 --> 00:34:53,360
Why are there frogs in my kitchen?!

474
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:56,400
I was going to make
spicy stir-fried frog for you,

475
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:59,880
but I accidentally dropped the container
and they got out.

476
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:01,480
What should I do?

477
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:09,120
Look.

478
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,920
Mom!

479
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:18,800
Oh my…

480
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:20,240
Mother?!

481
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:24,440
I've got them all now.

482
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:25,880
Thank you so much.

483
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:28,320
-Please release them somewhere safe.
-Of course.

484
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:32,760
Mother…

485
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:34,480
I'm really sorry.

486
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:37,120
Looks like spicy stir-fried frog
is off the menu.

487
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:39,040
You did this on purpose.

488
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,000
No, Mother.

489
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:43,280
I really wanted you to try it.

490
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:46,360
Frog is actually very good for older folks…

491
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:49,480
high protein, low fat, and rich in nutrients.

492
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:51,840
Good for brains and nerves.

493
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:55,720
It also strengthens bones and immunity…

494
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:57,360
so you won't die too soon.

495
00:35:57,680 --> 00:35:58,560
You…

496
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:02,360
rude, disrespectful!
Didn't your parents teach you anything?!

497
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:03,880
They did.

498
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:07,400
They taught me to be polite
only to people who deserve it.

499
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:10,880
And you're not one of them.

500
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:13,800
Runch…

501
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:16,920
Runch,

502
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:18,920
you can eat with your mom.

503
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,080
I'll go upstairs first.

504
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:25,080
Come up when you're done.

505
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,120
I've got a little treat for you.

506
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:37,920
Why didn't you say anything?

507
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:39,440
Mom…

508
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:42,080
I don't even know what to say anymore.

509
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:43,880
And I'm tired of it.

510
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:47,160
So you only listen to her now and not me?

511
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:50,760
Mom…

512
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:53,080
what do you want to eat?

513
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,840
I'll order it for you.

514
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:57,920
I won't eat anything. I don't want anything.

515
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,040
Neen…

516
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,120
If you're here to lecture me, don't.

517
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:27,760
I don't want to hear it.

518
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:35,480
Just hear me out…

519
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:56,280
What are you--

520
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:08,320
Oh, Runch… oh god…

521
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:10,120
Please stop…

522
00:38:11,120 --> 00:38:12,600
Neen, enough already.

523
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:15,160
What? But I don't want to stop yet.

524
00:38:15,160 --> 00:38:16,760
What are you doing?

525
00:38:17,240 --> 00:38:19,600
I'm going to make your mom go deaf
from my screaming.

526
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:23,320
Since she loves imagining things,
I'll make she go crazy this time.

527
00:38:25,600 --> 00:38:26,480
Neen…

528
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:32,640
Stop. She's going to misunderstand.

529
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:34,240
-Come here.
-Whoa!

530
00:38:34,240 --> 00:38:35,160
Ugh!

531
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:38,040
Runch, stop it… Ah--

532
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:38,920
Neen, enough.

533
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:40,760
What are you doing to my daughter?!

534
00:38:40,760 --> 00:38:41,600
Neen!

535
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:43,240
Open the door right now!

536
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:45,120
Open it!

537
00:38:45,200 --> 00:38:47,320
Leave us alone, Mother. I'm-- Ow!

538
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:49,680
Runch, don't bite me! That hurts!

539
00:38:49,680 --> 00:38:51,120
Open the door, Neen!

540
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:52,360
Open it right now!

541
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:55,600
Ow! You always bite me, Runch!

542
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:58,000
It hurts! Ow!

543
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,360
Hey, stop it.

544
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:05,760
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

545
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:09,800
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

546
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:15,720
♪ Every action conveys these words, you know? ♪

547
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:20,320
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

548
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:24,080
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

549
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:26,360
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

550
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:28,680
♪ Our touches… ♪

551
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:40,360
Are you having fun?

552
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,280
But right now,

553
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:52,680
you're getting yourself into trouble.

554
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:54,400
You know that, right?

555
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:57,640
Mm-hm.

556
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:20,960
I told you two to make up, not hook up.

557
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:22,640
Hey, watch it.

558
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:25,040
Why? Didn't you two…

559
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:26,840
last night?

560
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:28,640
You already know what happened.

561
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:31,880
So, did your hag-in-law know

562
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:35,120
what you and Runch were doing in that room?

563
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,000
Of course she did.

564
00:40:40,120 --> 00:40:42,120
I was loud on purpose.

565
00:40:42,120 --> 00:40:44,080
She probably couldn't sleep all night.

566
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:01,120
I was gone for one night
and you couldn't sleep?

567
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:02,520
Don't be ridiculous.

568
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:05,960
I couldn't sleep
because there was a demon in this house.

569
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:07,200
A demon?

570
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,160
What demon?

571
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:11,800
That spoiled brat stayed over
with Runch last night.

572
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:13,800
And she…

573
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:15,080
she…

574
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:20,040
she did shameless things in this house.

575
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:23,040
You saw them?

576
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,680
Of course I didn't see them! I heard them.

577
00:41:28,120 --> 00:41:29,400
All night long…

578
00:41:30,520 --> 00:41:32,600
she kept moaning Runch's name.

579
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:33,880
"Oh…"

580
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:35,240
"Ah…"

581
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:37,840
I nearly had a heart attack.

582
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:42,320
I think the most shameless thing here

583
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:43,960
was your behavior.

584
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:47,160
You eavesdropped them
on their private moment!

585
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:50,920
I wasn't trying to!

586
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,520
I was worried about our daughter.

587
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,840
Worried… or curious?

588
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:58,520
Curious about what exactly, Pong?

589
00:41:58,520 --> 00:42:00,680
What would I even be curious about?

590
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:03,440
I was afraid that woman
was putting some kind of spell on Runch.

591
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:07,880
I just came back from a meditation retreat
feeling peaceful,

592
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:11,640
and now you've reminded me of something else.

593
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:12,640
What?

594
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:16,200
Our daughter has her own life, honey.

595
00:42:16,920 --> 00:42:18,760
We don't own her.

596
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:21,880
We gave birth to her and raised her,

597
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,880
but we can't live her life for her.

598
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:27,480
Who she loves…

599
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:30,000
is up to her heart,

600
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:31,080
not you.

601
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:34,400
-But--
-I know you love Runch very much…

602
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:39,800
but it has made you controlling.

603
00:42:40,440 --> 00:42:42,840
That leaves her exhausted and uncomfortable.

604
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:47,440
If you keep this up,
you'll only push her farther away.

605
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,760
She's an adult now.

606
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:55,480
She gets to choose her own happiness,

607
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:58,600
not the one you choose for her.

608
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:02,040
Give her some space, Ging.

609
00:43:04,560 --> 00:43:05,920
I'll never do that.

610
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:09,680
If I did, I'd lose to that woman.

611
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:39,640
THREE YEARS AGO

612
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:40,920
Here's your shirt.

613
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:43,400
I already washed it. Thank you again.

614
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:45,600
You're welcome.

615
00:43:46,080 --> 00:43:49,040
Next time, be more careful with your coffee.

616
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:52,240
I will.

617
00:43:57,080 --> 00:43:58,080
Ms. Neen?

618
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:03,520
Yes?

619
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:13,120
What is it, Ms. Runch?

620
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:16,040
Are you free today?

621
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:20,040
If you don't mind,

622
00:44:20,400 --> 00:44:22,760
I'd like to treat you to a meal as thanks.

623
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:29,320
But it's okay if you're busy.

624
00:44:29,840 --> 00:44:31,600
Who said I'm busy?

625
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:35,160
If you want to treat me,

626
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:37,080
I'm not saying no.

627
00:44:41,120 --> 00:44:43,120
Now that we know each other better,

628
00:44:43,640 --> 00:44:45,440
let's stop being so formal.

629
00:44:46,600 --> 00:44:47,560
Big Sis Runch.

630
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:50,200
You're younger than me?

631
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:51,280
Of course I am.

632
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:57,080
Little Sis Neen…

633
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:00,360
Do you like that?

634
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:04,000
Depends on who's saying it.

635
00:45:05,160 --> 00:45:06,800
If it's you…

636
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:08,640
then I like it.

637
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:15,240
Actually, there's something else
I want to call you.

638
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:18,160
What is it?

639
00:45:19,240 --> 00:45:20,760
Beautiful.

640
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:27,360
You're really beautiful, Runch.

641
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:31,280
Thank you.

642
00:45:33,040 --> 00:45:34,080
I like you.

643
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:39,160
I mean… I like beautiful women.

644
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:45,840
I see.

645
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:48,560
Well…

646
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:50,240
I'm glad you like me.

647
00:45:57,160 --> 00:45:58,200
ONE NEW MESSAGE

648
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:00,200
Morning, beautiful.

649
00:46:00,440 --> 00:46:02,800
Don't forget your favorite coffee today.

650
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:07,600
♪ I love you more than words
But our path isn't easy ♪

651
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:10,800
♪ I just need you to believe in me ♪

652
00:46:10,800 --> 00:46:12,040
Got it.

653
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:14,840
♪ I'm weak for your lips ♪

654
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:18,840
♪ And the kiss upon my forehead ♪

655
00:46:18,880 --> 00:46:22,600
ONE NEW MESSAGE

656
00:46:22,800 --> 00:46:25,440
Have you had lunch yet, Neen?

657
00:46:26,520 --> 00:46:29,800
Not yet. I'm enjoying your attention first.

658
00:46:29,800 --> 00:46:33,120
♪ My love is in these soft whispers ♪

659
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:35,480
♪ You have to feel it with your heart ♪

660
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:39,320
♪ Our touches will make you understand ♪

661
00:46:39,320 --> 00:46:40,800
Sweet dreams, Runch.

662
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,960
♪ Can you hear me saying I love you? ♪

663
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,720
You too, Neen.

664
00:46:45,880 --> 00:46:50,320
♪ And you'll love so deeply ♪

665
00:46:50,360 --> 00:46:54,200
♪ Can you feel my love? ♪

666
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:59,640
♪ Please know that I love you ♪

667
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:07,320
I'm so happy to see you again.

668
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:08,480
Here.

669
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:13,360
Aren't you going to check your phone?

670
00:47:13,360 --> 00:47:16,800
No, I want to focus on dinner with you.

671
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:18,240
Hold my hand when we go in, okay?

672
00:47:19,040 --> 00:47:21,000
I can tell you're jealous.

673
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:23,440
Why would I be?
We're getting divorced anyway.

674
00:47:23,520 --> 00:47:25,280
You like Runch, don't you?

675
00:47:25,360 --> 00:47:26,400
Auntie!

676
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:31,280
Let's stay like this. It feels nice.

677
00:47:31,280 --> 00:47:34,080
♪ Living with pain and love ♪

678
00:47:34,120 --> 00:47:36,880
♪ Living while waiting and losing hope ♪

679
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:39,360
♪ A voice inside my heart says enough ♪

680
00:47:39,360 --> 00:47:42,440
♪ But another voice asks me to endure ♪

681
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:45,160
♪ I stay because I love you, you know? ♪

682
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:51,080
♪ I still believe in the love between us ♪

683
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:56,080
♪ Please let us go back to how we were ♪

684
00:47:56,080 --> 00:48:00,200
♪ I don't know if our love is just impossible ♪

685
00:48:00,200 --> 00:48:03,040
♪ Or if there's a reason for all of this ♪

686
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:07,200
♪ And that reason is you don't love me ♪
